About HomeTech Innovations
Your Eau Claire Area Audio/Visual Specialists
Mission Statement: HomeTech Innovations is committed to providing its customers with innovative solutions to meet their home audio/visual and automation needs. We keep this commitment by offering quality products, prompt service, and competitive pricing to meet the demands of any customer.
HomeTech Innovations is a locally owned and operated company located in Eau Claire, WI. We specialize in the design and installation of audio/visual systems, as well as home automation systems. We also sell a variety of audio/visual equipment, as an authorized dealer of several top audio/visual brands.
HomeTech Innovations is fully insured and employs trained and experienced technicians to design and install your home audio/visual or automation system. We are proud to have a growing customer base, including several local home builders.
Our work was featured in the 2012 Chippewa Valley Home Builders Association's Parade of Homes and we're working on highlighting more our our products and services in the 2013 Parade of Homes. We are a member of the Chippewa Valley Home Builders Association, and are ELAN and LUTRON Certified for home automation and lighting systems installation.
From Our Customers
"Garrett and Hunter were great to work with in purchasing and installing of our Niles Sound System
and our Graber Blinds.  Both of them went out of their way explaining each product as well as the benefits
of the sound system. They were always a phone call away when we had any questions including those
with our newly-purchased smart tv and their patience with us was impressive.  We consider Garrett and
Hunter to be our friends now and would highly recommend them to anyone in need of either of these services.
Thank you so much!"
- Judith Fletschock
"We had the pleasure of working with HomeTech Innovations LLC while we were building our home. Right from the start it was clear, both Hunter and Garrett love what they do and are very knowledgeable in their field. They provided us with wiring and equipment for our TV, Internet, multi-zone home audio sound, as well as a home theater system."
- Kim
"I knew that I wanted to pre-wire our home when we built it to be sure to take advantage of getting all the wiring we “may” need installed before it was finished. Our relationship started there and Hunter guided us through every step in our selections. He helped us pick locations to wire to in each room in order to be sure to have the best location for TV’s and data ports. He provided valuable suggestions and input on setting up our home theater area in our new home, and even helped us pick out the right TV and home theater for us…to fit our budget. Our plan wasn’t the best but HomeTech made it great. After complete in home installation and setup, Hunter took care of us with questions and concerns. I am definitely impressed with their service and knowledge and would recommend them hands down."
- Jeff





