Labor and Skills Deficits in Construction: Not just at Jobsite Level
While construction labor shortages are getting a lot of warranted press lately, it’s also very apparent that the industry is suffering from a lack of experienced and skilled staff at the supervisory and project management levels. A lot of talent left construction during the Great Recession, and while the industry is rebounding, the talent pool may not have caught up with the improving economic climate. Find out what a recent Home Innovation focus group with ASHRAE members revealed about this situation. 
